race.comment: SILVERTURN (6) has returned in good order this prep, finding the frame here in her two runs back. Peaking now and is ready to break through. LIGHT MY LIFE (10) was doing her best work late here on debut, closing off nicely over the concluding stages to grab third. Is sure to have come on with that run under her belt and is capable of going a couple better this time. ADAJ (9) caught the eye first-up at Townsville when warming nicely late to earn a minor cheque. Drawn much kinder this time and can give this a big shake. WEBS (8) was better last time at Ewan. Similar effort here makes her competitive.
